== Shorshe Ilish (hilsa mustard curry) ==

note over Skillet #FFF9E6
T: 20:25:00
Ingredients (with measures):
- 1.0–1.2 kg hilsa, cut into 6–8 steaks (or purchased steaks)
- 1 tsp turmeric (for fish)
- 1 tsp salt (for fish; adjust)
- 60 ml mustard oil (total)
- 1/2 tsp nigella seeds (kalonji) OR 1 tsp panch phoron (optional)
- Mustard paste (from earlier): ~120 ml (about 1/2 cup)
- 250 ml water (to loosen gravy)
- 4 green chillies, slit
end note

note over Skillet #E0F7FF
Equipment:
- PrepBoard, Skillet, Hob, Bowl
- Fish slice/spatula, lid, timer
end note

Refrigerator -> PrepBoard: Retrieve hilsa; pat dry; cut into steaks if needed\nT: 20:25:00, 00:06:00, M:1.0–1.2 kg hilsa, A:gently, E:paper towel
Pantry -> PrepBoard: Season fish with turmeric + salt\nT: 20:31:00, 00:02:00, M:1 tsp turmeric + 1 tsp salt, A:evenly coated, E:
Pantry -> Skillet: Add mustard oil and heat until shimmering\nT: 20:33:00, 00:02:00, M:60 ml mustard oil, A:hot, E:ventilate
Skillet -> Hob: Temper nigella seeds (or panch phoron) briefly\nT: 20:35:00, 00:00:20, M:1/2 tsp nigella (or 1 tsp panch phoron), A:briefly, E:
PrepBoard -> Skillet: Add hilsa steaks; sear very lightly (optional)\nT: 20:35:20, 00:03:00, M:6–8 fish steaks, A:lightly, E:handle carefully
Bowl -> Skillet: Add mustard paste + water to form gravy\nT: 20:38:20, 00:01:00, M:120 ml mustard paste + 250 ml water, A:stirred smooth, E:
PrepBoard -> Skillet: Add slit green chillies; cover\nT: 20:39:20, 00:00:30, M:4 green chillies, A:, E:lid on
Skillet -> Hob: Simmer gently until fish just cooked\nT: 20:39:50, 00:08:00, M:gentle simmer, A:do not over-stir, E:lid on
Hob --> Skillet: Fish cooked; gravy thickened slightly\nT: 20:47:50, 00:00:10, M:just-flaking fish, A:, E:
Skillet -> Hob: Rest off heat to settle gravy\nT: 20:48:00, 00:05:00, M:rested curry, A:undisturbed, E:

